<h2>What Data We Store</h2>
<p>
    Taskque stores only task-related data to support basic task management functionality. This includes:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>Task titles and descriptions</li>
    <li>Task status (To Do, In Progress, Done)</li>
    <li>Priority levels</li>
    <li>Due dates</li>
    <li>Assigned users (Azure AD user IDs or emails)</li>
    <li>Task creation and update timestamps</li>
</ul>
<p>
    No sensitive personal data such as passwords, addresses, or payment information is collected or stored.
</p>

<h2>How Your Data Is Protected</h2>
<p>
    Taskque uses <strong>Microsoft Entra ID</strong> (formerly Azure Active Directory) to provide secure authentication and authorization.
</p>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Authentication:</strong> Only authenticated users via Entra ID can access the app.</li>
    <li>
        <strong>Authorization:</strong> Role-based access ensures that:
        <ul>
            <li>Admins can view and manage all tasks</li>
            <li>Regular users can view and manage only their own tasks</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Microsoft Entra ID uses industry-standard OAuth 2.0 and OpenID Connect protocols.
</p>


<h2>Cookies and Tracking</h2>
<p>
    This application does <strong>not</strong> use cookies, third-party tracking, or analytics tools.
</p>

